article.headline: Northeastern 71, Maine 61
article.story: BOSTON (AP) -- Bennet Davis had 19 points and four blocks and Bobby Kelly added 17 points to lead Northeastern to a 71-61 win over Maine on Saturday. Adrian Martinez scored 11 and Manny Adako had eight points and 10 rebounds for the Huskies, who have won three of four. Northeastern (10-18, 7-9 Colonial Athletic Association) outscored Maine (11-16, 6-8 America East) 35-19 in the first half, using early runs of 12-0 and 8-0 to blow it open. After falling behind 4-0, Northeastern scored 12 straight. Kelly made two 3-pointers during that stretch, and his second 3-pointer gave the Huskies a 12-4 lead with 15:28 left in the half. Maine then pulled to within 14-8, but Northeastern responded with an 8-0 spurt to extend its lead. Adako's jumper with 9:25 left put the Huskies up 22-8. Black Bears leading scorer Kevin Reed shot 5-for-17 from the field for 14 points. He was 2-for-10 in the first half, as the Black Bears shot 28 percent. Maine pulled to within seven points twice in the closing minutes, but Davis sank two free throws both times to ice the Northeastern win. Chris Bruff scored 12 and Mark Socoby added 11 for Maine, which has lost four straight.
